<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: IwantaGBS</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-29 22:13:53</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I've hunted her for 5 days, which is about 35 hrs online for me (ok, I play EQ too much).<BR>
<BR>
I've seen her 7 times and killed her 6.  Can't underestimate the value of a ranger willing to track for a piece of the pie.<BR>
<BR>
She's heavily camped, but most people give up after a couple of nights due to the sheer boredom of camping the ruins.  These haven't been my most exciting days in EQ, but it's like winning the lotto if you get a GBS at my level, 22.<BR>
<BR>
Due to the semi-random nature of her spawn, I worry everyday that some newbie is gonna kill her and get the stone and sell it to a vendor while I'm at work or asleep.<BR>
<BR>
There does seem to be a connection between her and the other NPCs in the area...I've seen her too many times, based on the way I hunt her, for there not to be.(that's a hint, by the way)<BR>
<BR>
Since I haven't gotten the stone, I can't say that there's a way to make it drop, but I suspect it is simply a rare random and the only way to get it is to be patient, and I mean the kind of patient that is necessary when you watch grass grow. For the level 40 to 60 campers that want the GBS, I would suggest you buy it...prolly take less time to recoup the money than to camp the spawn.  I currently have an offer for a SMR and 2 FBSS when I get the GBS, so that's a guage for the value, or at least someones desperation.<BR>
<BR>
If you are camping the ruins and someone else shows up, don't act like you have a right to tell them to leave. Someone tried that with me today, because they had been there for 6 hrs...6 hrs on Pyzjn is like going through the drive-thru at McDonalds.  You just gotta hope you see her first.<BR>
<BR>
She has multiple spawn spots...I have confirmed 3, and have heard that there is at least 1 more.<BR>
<BR>
With regard to speculation, I fear that Varsoon may be involved, as the spell Identify shows this to be the black heart of Varsoon.  I have confirmed this identification with someone who owns the stone. Though he didn't kill Varsoon, he wasn't sure if someone had prior to him killing Pyzjn. Maybe he has to spawn and be killed for her to get his heart.  This would also make a bit of sense, since a level 12 necro dropping this kind of item seems a bit odd and Varsoon is a bad dude, especially when he returns as Varsoon the Undying.  I hope this turns out to be wrong, because that means I am wasting my time repeatedly killing Pyzjn.<BR>
<BR>
Once I have the stone, I will return and post ALL the details of my experience hunting Pyzjn. I am taking diligent notes of all things that occur while I am camping, so those who want to depend on the info provided, check back here often and look for a follow-up.<BR>
<BR>
I wish all of you luck in your hunt for this illusive item.  Also, if anyone who has the stone can give any definate info regarding your success, there seems to be a lot of interested people who would be very greatful...myself included.<BR>
<BR>
Just my 2cp...hope you folks don't mind.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
