<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Okay here is what I have personally found out. Im sure that all this might have been mentioned throughout all the messages but just wanted to add my two cents. Anyways, today i set out to camp for the GBS because I am in some serious needs of cash. It was earlier in the morning about 8 eq time. I killed everything that wandered near the ruins or spawned in the ruins and even went a little ways away from the ruins to kill as well so i killed everything in a very large radius. As for the mentionings of all the other npc's being placeholders my research shows this as being false. I camped her tonight for 4 eq nights in a row and she spawned every time! All I did was kill kill kill. Of course i wasn't very lucky and she never dropped the Gbd any of the 4 times so i assume the drop has to be ultra rare. A freind of mine said drop ratio is about 1:10. Anyways I hope this helps all of you fellow hunters and goodluck bagging your GBS.<BR>
