<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Ending Dawn</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-04 01:38:43</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I finally got the glowing black stone after 3 weeks, off and on. I killed that lil necro more than a dozen times ( completely ruining any chance of setting foot in the necro guild in Qeynos).<BR>
I spent about 50 Hrs total at the ruins.  I went after Tovax in the begining, running over when ever someone spotted him.  But after reading these posts i realized it was more than likely a waste of time.<BR>
I decided to try a new approch and concentrate on the ruins area itself.  I sat in the middle of the ruins and killed everything that moved at night and during the day i went into town to refuel and offload the coppers.<BR>
( From my experinces, I've rarely seen her in the daylight.) This last camp I sat through two full EQ days clearing the ruins and no sign of her.  It was almost morning when i saw here stroling up from the bottem of the hill from the direction of surefall.<BR>
She went down fast with the necro drain spells, beating out a lvl 15 KS'r who happened on her while i was fighting.  I didn't even wait for her to hit the ground before I was looting, and there it was. The black pearl of my dreams, right next to the <BR>
Stupid rusty dagger. hehe  I don't think there is any rhyme or reason to it, just luck and persistance.  Good luck to all who try for it.<BR>
<BR>
Ending Dawn (21 human necromancer)<BR>
Tunare server</font></td></tr></table>
